The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as instance segmentation and semantic segmentation, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also introduces a new operator that is trainable end-to-end, which suggests a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely categories as well. The experiments conducted in the paper involve clothing parsing and street scene segmentation, which are both subfields of computer vision and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also mentions Cityscapes, a self-driving dataset, which suggests a possible connection to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
